etymologies: late 19th century: imitative of its call

definitions: a large tyrant flycatcher with a black-and-white-striped head and bright yellow breast, found mainly in tropical America.

notes.text: The greater kiskadee (Pitangus sulphuratus) and the lesser kiskadee (Philohydor lictor), family Tyrannidae

shortDefinitions: large tyrant flycatcher with black-and-white-striped head and bright yellow breast
